primaryTopic.definition: The Center's location is an ideal setting for our scientists and students to conduct their research -- much of which focuses on understanding the natural forces at work in the San Francisco Bay and its surrounding wetland environments. RTC research scientists are also studying natural phenomena in the open ocean; along California's coastline and in remote locations such as the Ross Sea (Antarctica) and the Equatorial Pacific.
